Date: 27 Aug 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, 26 Aug 2005, Vol. 18 - No. 34 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/a_current.htm#Sec7>

Foot and mouth disease in Myanmar, virus type Asia 1
-----------------------------------------------
Immediate notification report and final report.
Information received on 25 Aug 2005 from Dr. U. Maung Maung Nyunt, Director
General, Livestock Breeding and Veterinary Department, Ministry of
Livestock and Fisheries, Yangon:
Report date: 25 Aug 2005.
Precise identification of agent: foot and mouth disease (FMD) virus type
Asia 1.
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 4 Aug 2005.
Date of start of the event: 27 Jul 2005.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.
Details of outbreaks:
1st administrative division (State): Kayah
Lower administrative division (district): Loikaw
Type of epidemiological unit: village
Name of the location: Daw paw ka law
Date of start of the outbreak: 27 Jul 2005
Species: bov
Number of animals in the outbreaks:
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
493 / 10 / ... / ... / ...
1st administrative division (State): Kayah
Lower administrative division (district): Loikaw
Type of epidemiological unit: village
Name of the location: Pan kan
Date of start of the outbreak: 28 Jul 2005
Species: bov
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
352 / 10 / ... / ... / ...
1st administrative division (State): Kayah
Lower administrative division (district): Demawhsoe
Type of epidemiological unit: village
Name of the location: Kalthawdaw
Date of start of the outbreak: 29 Jul 2005
Species: bov
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
153 / 2 / ... / ... / ...
Diagnosis:
Laboratory where diagnosis was made: FMD Laboratory, Insein, Yangon
Diagnostic tests used: indirect sandwich ELISA (1)
Date: 4 Aug 2005
Results: Asia 1 positive
Source of outbreaks or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive.
Control measures:
A. Undertaken:
- quarantine;
- movement control inside the country;
- disinfection of infected premises/establishments;
- dipping/spraying.
B. To be undertaken: vaccination.
Treatment of affected animals: yes (palliative treatment for secondary
infections, feeding concentrate and tonic mixtures).
Final report: yes (the outbreaks have ceased and the disease is well
controlled, there has been no spread to other areas).
(1) ELISA: enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay
Note by the OIE Animal Health Information Department: the previous outbreak
of FMD due to virus type Asia 1 in Myanmar was in 2001.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Unfortunately, the 1st and final report are one and the same. - Mod.PC]
